News – Software Design and Collaboration Laboratory SDCL Software Design and Collaboration Laboratory News New Scholarships Posted by andre on February 3, 2014 at 10:55 am Congratulations to Nick Lopez and Christian Adriano, who were recently granted the 2014 Miguel Velez scholarship. New workshop on Crowdsourcing in Software Engineering Posted by andre on December 8, 2013 at 5:27 pm Thomas is co-organizing a new workshop on Crowdsourcing in Software Engineering (CSI-SE), in conjunction with ICSE 2014. The workshop will be a one day event with invited talks, a poster and demos session, and a crowd-based working session giving participants the opportunity to explore the application of crowdsourcing to software engineering and begin to forge […] Paper on Calico to appear at CHI 2014! Posted by andre on December 8, 2013 at 5:21 pm Our paper, Supporting Informal Design with Interactive Whiteboards, was accepted for inclusion at CHI 2014! Hope to see you in Toronto! 2013 ACM Distinguished Scientists Posted by andre on November 20, 2013 at 1:47 pm André was recognized as one of the 2013 ACM Distinguished Scientists. A big congratulations to André! ACM announcement Article published in Empirical Software Engineering Journal Posted by andre on October 1, 2013 at 11:20 am Looking to evaluate a software engineering tool in a study with developers? Check out our new ESE journal article for options, standard practices, and tradeoffs, grounded in a literature review of over 1700 software engineering papers. article Welcome Namrata! Posted by andre on September 29, 2013 at 9:44 pm We are very excited to welcome Namrata Puri to the laboratory. She is joining us as a new M.S. student and will be working on the UI of CodeExchange. Congrats Dr. Nick! Posted by andre on September 18, 2013 at 5:49 pm Congratulations to Nick Mangano, who successfully defended his Ph.D. dissertation entitled ‘Calico: an early-phase software design tool’ on September 18, with a committee of Gary Olson, David Redmiles, and Marian Petre (in addition to his advisor, of course). After 6 years of very hard work, Nick is now off to make a commercial version of […] CrowdCode at CrowdConf Posted by andre on September 11, 2013 at 9:23 pm Our abstract, CrowdCode: A platform for crowd development, was selected for both a poster and a talk at CrowdConf! Hope to see you in San Francisco. ISR Research Forum Posted by andre on May 30, 2013 at 9:21 pm SDCL is excited to welcome visitors to our lab for the ISR Research Forum. We have demos lined up of several of our research projects and are looking forward to exchanging ideas with both fellow researchers and developers from industry. If you’re in Irvine, we hope to see you there! Lionel Briand visit Posted by andre on May 17, 2013 at 10:12 am Lionel Briand visited the SDCL as part of his visit as an ISR Distinguished Speaker. Once more, we had great interactions and discussions about our research. « Previous Page Next Page » Collaborators Anita Sarma Brandy Aven Crista Lopes David Redmiles Jim Herbsleb Laura Dabbish Linda Argote Marian Petre Na Meng Thomas LaToza Home Research CrowdDesign Crowd Debugging CodeExchange PorchLight Past projects Lighthouse Calico Code Orb Crowd Development Papers Technical reports Dissertations Books Opportunities MDP Lab Study Materials and Data KnoCap People Previous members Sponsors Contact Directions The Software Design and Collaboration Laboratory is housed in the Department of Informatics in the Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences at the University of California, Irvine. Copyright © SDCL | eDegree° Theme by Top Blog Formula on WordPress | Log In